FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784751301
OL,3,CSecond Wimbledon expansion challenge
OL,4,Cgranted by judge
OL,6,FIn March, Mr Justice Thompsell ruled
OL,7,Fthe land was "unencumbered by any
OL,8,Fstatutory trust" but the Court of
OL,9,FAppeal has granted SWP permission to
OL,10,Fchallenge the ruling.
OL,12,FIn a court order, Lord Justice Newey
OL,13,Fsaid:
OL,15,F"The arguments advanced by the
OL,16,Fappellant have sufficient substance
OL,17,Ffor the appeal to have a real prospect
OL,18,Fof success."
OL,26,@oD@NOUpD@PO]wD@AOUzD@LO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/8
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784751301
OL,3,CSecond Wimbledon expansion challenge
OL,4,Cgranted by judge
OL,6,FThe order states that the appeal is
OL,7,Fexpected to last three days, with SWP
OL,8,Fsaying the hearing is expected to be
OL,9,Fheld in 2027.
OL,11,FSWP said on Wednesday that the All
OL,12,FEngland Club "has been saying in
OL,13,Fpublic and to their members that
OL,14,Fproceeding with their plans was a
OL,15,Fforegone conclusion" but the Court of
OL,16,FAppeal's decision showed this to be
OL,17,F"wishful thinking".
OL,19,FA spokesperson for the All England
OL,20,FClub said the decision was
OL,21,F"disappointing news" but said it was:
OL,26,@tD@NOUwD@TO]yD@AOUyD@RO]}D@AOU}D@TO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/8
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784751301
OL,3,CSecond Wimbledon expansion challenge
OL,4,Cgranted by judge
OL,6,F"Confident that the Court of Appeal
OL,7,Fwill recognise the strength of the
OL,8,FHigh Court ruling, which found by a
OL,9,Fwide margin that the golf course land
OL,10,Fhad never been held under a statutory
OL,11,Ftrust.
OL,13,F"The vast majority of local people
OL,14,Fsimply want us to get on and deliver
OL,15,Fthe significant community benefits on
OL,16,Foffer as soon as possible and they
OL,17,Fwill naturally be disappointed that
OL,18,Fthis decision will inevitably lead to
OL,19,Ffurther delays.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/8
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,372,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F371A1784751301
OL,3,CSecond Wimbledon expansion challenge
OL,4,Cgranted by judge
OL,6,F"It is firmly in the public and local
OL,7,Fcommunity's interest that the scheme
OL,8,Fis delivered in full."
OL,10,FBarristers for SWP told the High Court
OL,11,Fin January that a statutory trust
OL,12,Fexists under the Public Health Act
OL,13,F1875, meaning the land must be used
OL,14,F"for the purpose of being used as
OL,15,Fpublic walks or pleasure grounds" and
OL,16,Ftherefore the development could not go
OL,17,Fahead.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@VO]vD@AOUwD@aO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/8
